---
description: LangGraph multi-agent pipeline rules
globs: ["backend/pipeline/**/*.py"]
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use LangGraph StateGraph API (v0.2+). Never use deprecated AgentExecutor / initialize_agent.
- Shared state is a single typed TypedDict; each node takes state and returns a partial state update.
- One agent = one node = one responsibility. Order: ingestion -> features -> anomaly -> (conditional) narrative -> dispatch.
- Conditional edges skip narrative + dispatch when risk_score <= 65.
- Each agent is importable and unit-testable in isolation.
- Verify any LangGraph/LangChain function exists in the installed version before using it; these APIs change often.
